        <!-------Testimonial End-------> 

        <!-------FAQ Start------->
        <section class="faq section-padding prelative" data-scroll-index='4'>
          <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
              <div class="col-md-12">
                <div class="sectioner-header text-center">
                  <h3>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h3>
                  <span class="line"></span>
                  <p>Got questions? We've got answers! Check out our FAQ section for all the information you need to plan your perfect trip to Manzanillo, Colima. From the best time to visit to transportation options and more, we've got you covered. Can't find what you're looking for? Feel free to reach out to us directly, and we'll be happy to assist you.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="section-content">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s">
                      <h4>What is the best time to visit Manzanillo, Colima?</h4>
                      <p>The best time to visit Manzanillo is during the dry season, from November to April. During these months, the weather is more pleasant with moderate temperatures and less chance of rain.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.2s">
                      <h4>What are the must-do tourist activities in Manzanillo?</h4>
                      <p>you can't miss: Enjoying the beautiful beaches like Playa La Audiencia and Playa Miramar, or engaging in water sports such as snorkeling, diving, and sport fishing, you also shouldn't miss visiting the historic downtown and the Manzanillo boardwalk!</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s">
                      <h4>Is it safe to travel to Manzanillo?</h4>
                      <p>Yes, Manzanillo is generally safe for tourists. As with any destination, it's advisable to take basic precautions such as not displaying valuables, staying in well-lit areas at night, and following local recommendations.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.4s">
                      <h4>What transportation options are available in Manzanillo?</h4>
                      <p>Manzanillo offers several transportation options, including taxis, buses, and private transportation services like Uber. Renting a car is also possible for greater convenience and flexibility in your travels.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s">
                      <h4>What type of cuisine can I find in Manzanillo?</h4>
                      <p>Manzanillo is famous for its seafood-based cuisine. Dishes you must try include ceviche, pescado zarandeado, shrimp tacos, and tuba, a traditional regional drink.</p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6 faq-content wow fadeInUp" data-wow-delay="0.6s">
                      <h4>What are the accommodation options in Manzanillo?</h4>
                      <p>Manzanillo offers a wide variety of accommodation options, from luxury hotels and all-inclusive resorts to hostels and vacation rentals. There is something for every type of traveler and budget.</p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </section>

        <!-------FAQ End-------> 

